libfilezilla
------------------------------------------
libfilezilla is a small and modern C++ library, offering some basic
functionality to build high-performing, platform-independent programs. Some of
the highlights include:
 * A typesafe, multi-threaded event system that's very simple to use yet
   extremely efficient
 * Timers for periodic events
 * A datetime class that not only tracks timestamp but also their accuracy,
   which simplifies dealing with timestamps originating from different sources
 * Simple process handling for spawning child processes with redirected I/O

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.4.1-1
  cygwin-devel-2.4.1-1
  libfilezilla-devel-0.4.0.1-1bl1
  libfilezilla0-0.4.0.1-1bl1
  libgcc1-5.3.0-3
  libiconv-devel-1.14-3
  libiconv2-1.14-3
  libstdc++6-5.3.0-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-5.3.0-3
  gcc-g++-5.3.0-3
  libtool-2.4.6-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://lib.filezilla-project.org/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/filezilla/libfilezilla-0.4.0.1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libfilezilla-0.4.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libfilezilla-0.4.0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libfilezilla-0.4.0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfilezilla-0.4.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfilezilla0-0.4.0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfilezilla-devel-0.4.0.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

